ege Orientation Workshop  A member of the VMI Class of 1958  Witt served as a trustee the VMI Foundation from 1988 to 1994 and a member of the executive committee of the Reveille  A Call to Excel campaign  Witt also chaired the Class of 1958 s 50th Reunion Fund  From 1994 to 2005  Witt was a member of the VMI Board of Visitors  serving as its president from 2001 to 2005  During that time  he headed the effort to recruit the fourteenth superintendent of VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 